22
00:00:59.108 --> 00:01:01.290
NOVA:  What exactly is a 'log'?

23
00:01:01.590 --> 00:01:04.546
VEGA:  A diary the system keeps. A Windows Event

24
00:01:04.546 --> 00:01:07.069
Log, a syslog, a tool like Splunk -

25
00:01:07.069 --> 00:01:07.790
same idea.

26
00:01:08.840 --> 00:01:11.400
VEGA:  AU-2 chooses what's worth logging.

27
00:01:11.700 --> 00:01:14.482
NULL:  So I'll just delete the logs when I'm

28
00:01:14.482 --> 00:01:14.858
done.

29
00:01:15.908 --> 00:01:19.668
VEGA:  Not so fast. AU-9 protects the logs themselves.

30
00:01:19.968 --> 00:01:22.830
NOVA:  So the Null can't quietly rewrite history.

31
00:01:23.880 --> 00:01:26.608
ARCHIVIST:  Identify the types of events that the system

32
00:01:26.608 --> 00:01:29.026
is capable of logging in support of the

33
00:01:29.026 --> 00:01:29.956
audit function:

34
00:01:31.006 --> 00:01:32.876
VEGA:  A log no one reads, or one that

35
00:01:32.876 --> 00:01:34.806
can be erased, is no log at all.

36
00:01:41.306 --> 00:01:44.599
VEGA:  The Chronicler's oath. Every footstep written; no page

37
00:01:44.599 --> 00:01:45.026
erased.

38
00:01:46.076 --> 00:01:49.036
VEGA:  The Healer, System and Information Integrity.

39
00:01:49.336 --> 00:01:52.340
NOVA:  It finds the rot, cures the sickness, and

40
00:01:52.340 --> 00:01:53.878
keeps the truth true.

41
00:01:54.178 --> 00:01:57.633
VEGA:  In reality, that's patching flaws, blocking malicious code,

42
00:01:57.633 --> 00:02:01.205
monitoring for intrusions, and verifying nothing was tampered

43
00:02:01.205 --> 00:02:01.498
with.

44
00:02:02.548 --> 00:02:06.748
VEGA:  SI-2 is flaw remediation, the discipline of patching.

45
00:02:09.048 --> 00:02:11.725
VEGA:  And SI-4 watches the system for signs of

46
00:02:11.725 --> 00:02:12.528
an intruder.

47
00:02:12.828 --> 00:02:16.721
NULL:  Another tower turns? Tedious. Every chain of watchers

48
00:02:16.721 --> 00:02:18.851
has a blind link - and I will

49
00:02:18.851 --> 00:02:20.026
slip through it.

50
00:02:21.076 --> 00:02:24.662
NULL:  Six days in your shadows... and you still

51
00:02:24.662 --> 00:02:26.674
don't know what I took.

52
00:02:26.974 --> 00:02:29.276
NOVA:  Wait - six whole days?!

53
00:02:29.576 --> 00:02:32.353
VEGA:  Six days - but SI-4 saw the anomaly,

54
00:02:32.353 --> 00:02:35.053
and AU-9 kept the logs of his every

55
00:02:35.053 --> 00:02:37.445
step. He got in. He did not get

56
00:02:37.445 --> 00:02:38.216
out clean.

57
00:02:38.516 --> 00:02:39.994
NULL:  Clean enough... this time.

58
00:02:41.044 --> 00:02:45.400
ARCHIVIST:  Identify, report, and correct system flaws;

59
00:02:46.450 --> 00:02:49.530
VEGA:  Integrity is keeping the system clean and honest.

60
00:02:56.750 --> 00:02:59.135
VEGA:  The Healer's oath. Find the rot, close the

61
00:02:59.135 --> 00:03:00.270
wound, keep it true.

62
00:03:01.320 --> 00:03:03.440
VEGA:  The Firewatch, Incident Response.

63
00:03:03.740 --> 00:03:06.412
VEGA:  When something burns, it sounds the alarm and

64
00:03:06.412 --> 00:03:07.540
contains the blaze.

65
00:03:07.840 --> 00:03:12.228
VEGA:  In reality, that's detecting, reporting, analyzing, containing, and

66
00:03:12.228 --> 00:03:14.520
recovering from security incidents.

67
00:03:15.570 --> 00:03:18.152
NOVA:  When does a threat become an 'incident'?

68
00:03:18.452 --> 00:03:21.411
VEGA:  The moment it stops being hypothetical - malware

69
00:03:21.411 --> 00:03:23.692
runs, data leaks, a system goes down.

70
00:03:24.742 --> 00:03:27.324
NOVA:  What happens the moment we spot the Null?

71
00:03:27.624 --> 00:03:31.261
VEGA:  IR-4 takes over, handling the incident end to

72
00:03:31.261 --> 00:03:31.584
end.

73
00:03:32.634 --> 00:03:37.696
VEGA:  Every incident follows a rhythm: prepare, detect, contain,

74
00:03:37.696 --> 00:03:39.354
eradicate, recover.

75
00:03:39.654 --> 00:03:42.327
NOVA:  Is there a plan that makes all that

76
00:03:42.327 --> 00:03:43.396
routine? IR-8?

77
00:03:44.446 --> 00:03:48.474
ARCHIVIST:  Implement an incident handling capability for incidents that

78
00:03:48.474 --> 00:03:51.763
is consistent with the incident response plan and

79
00:03:51.763 --> 00:03:56.798
includes preparation, detection and analysis, containment, eradication, and

80
00:03:56.798 --> 00:03:57.402
recovery;

81
00:03:58.452 --> 00:04:01.412
VEGA:  The best responders practiced before the fire.

82
00:04:08.752 --> 00:04:11.405
VEGA:  The Firewatch's oath. When it burns, we are

83
00:04:11.405 --> 00:04:12.392
already running.

84
00:04:13.442 --> 00:04:16.960
VEGA:  Selecting and implementing was the wall. Watching is

85
00:04:16.960 --> 00:04:18.042
how you keep it.

86
00:04:22.042 --> 00:04:26.224
NOVA:  Scenario: the Null deletes logs. What stops it?

87
00:04:26.524 --> 00:04:28.967
An intruder tries to delete the logs to

88
00:04:28.967 --> 00:04:30.972
hide. Which control blocks that?

89
00:04:31.272 --> 00:04:35.581
Your options. A. AU-2 Event Logging. B. AU-9

90
00:04:35.581 --> 00:04:41.360
Protection of Audit Information. C. SI-4 System Monitoring.

91
00:04:41.660 --> 00:04:44.562
NOVA:  Pause here and lock in your answer.

92
00:04:51.612 --> 00:04:54.360
VEGA:  The answer is B. AU-9 Protection of Audit

93
00:04:54.360 --> 00:04:58.382
Information. AU-9, Protection of Audit Information, keeps an

94
00:04:58.382 --> 00:05:01.332
intruder from deleting or altering the logs.

95
00:05:02.382 --> 00:05:04.422
VEGA:  And who runs toward the fire?

96
00:05:04.722 --> 00:05:08.598
Which family detects, contains, and recovers from a

97
00:05:08.598 --> 00:05:09.130
breach?

98
00:05:09.430 --> 00:05:13.602
Your options. A. IR - Incident Response. B.

99
00:05:13.602 --> 00:05:16.998
AU - Audit. C. AC - Access Control.

100
00:05:17.298 --> 00:05:20.200
NOVA:  Pause here and lock in your answer.

101
00:05:27.250 --> 00:05:30.030
VEGA:  The answer is A. IR - Incident Response.

102
00:05:30.030 --> 00:05:33.853
Incident Response is the family that detects, contains,

103
00:05:33.853 --> 00:05:35.730
and recovers from a breach.

104
00:05:36.780 --> 00:05:39.764
NOVA:  Notebook: assume they got in, then see them,

105
00:05:39.764 --> 00:05:42.002
heal the system, and answer fast.

106
00:05:42.302 --> 00:05:45.582
VEGA:  Seen, healed, and answered. The towers hold.

107
00:05:45.882 --> 00:05:48.800
NULL:  Then I'll turn your own people against you.

108
00:05:49.100 --> 00:05:51.157
VEGA:  Then we ride to the Keepers of the

109
00:05:51.157 --> 00:05:51.460
Pact.
